'''Umorihiko Shrine''' (うもりひこじんじゃ) is a shrine located in {{ill|lt=Hatta-chō|Q11390732|WD=Q11390732|1=Hata, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima|Q207309|WD=Q207309|1=Tokushima (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* '''Uganomori no Kami''' - also said to be another name for {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ugayafukiaezu no Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}.

=== History ===
The founding date is unknown. It is an {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Engishiki shrine|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286|lt=Shikinaisha}}. This old shrine was also called "Umori Daimyōjin" and "Moritoki Daimyōjin." Flooding of the nearby {{ill|lt=Hatta River (Tokushima Prefecture)|Q11390730|WD=Q11390730|lt=Hatta River|1=Hata River}} caused the loss of the shrine buildings and old documents. In 1875 (Meiji 8), it was ranked as a {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

